FBIS4-43982 "drweu122aa_94002" FBIS-WEU-94-122 Daily Report 23 Jun 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Italy Conditionally Pledges Troops Italy Conditionally Pledges Troops LD2306163994 Paris France-Inter Radio Network in French 1600 GMT 23 Jun 94 LD2306163994 Paris France-Inter Radio Network French BFN [Text] Italian Prime Minister Silvio Berlusconi announced today that he is ready to provide 450 soldiers to carry out humanitarian work without entering Rwandan territory. Other countries, such as Israel and Egypt, have hailed the French initiative. Egypt said that it is ready to participate. Two other African countries, Senegal and Guinea, have promised to send men to the spot. Ghana is also expected to take part.
